definition: Iodine atom is the chemical element with atomic number 53.
description: Iodine is a chemical element; it has symbol I and atomic number 53. The heaviest of the stable halogens, it exists at standard conditions as a semi-lustrous, non-metallic solid that melts to form a deep violet liquid at 114 째C (237 째F), and boils to a violet gas at 184 째C (363 째F). [adapted from Wikipedia (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iodine)]
